CARD 21

True or False: Climate-adjusted provenancing means collecting from the exact same altitude and rainfall as the planting site.

A) True
B) False

<details>
<summary>✅ Answer</summary>
**B) False** – Climate-adjusted provenancing collects from slightly warmer/drier areas to future-proof restoration against climate change, rather than matching current conditions exactly.
</details>

