CARD 22

How should you clean fleshy fruits (Type A)?

A) Oven dry at 70°C
B) Macerate, ferment, float off pulp, rinse, dry
C) Sieve and winnow
D) Shake vigorously in a bag

<details>
<summary>✅ Answer</summary>
**B) Macerate, ferment, float off pulp, rinse, dry** – Remove all flesh to prevent mould. Some species may need 1-3 days fermentation.
</details>

