CARD 23

What is the correct action if you find nesting birds in a target collection tree?

A) Collect carefully to avoid disturbing the nest
B) Delay collection until after breeding season
C) Scare the birds away temporarily
D) Collect from the opposite side of the tree

<details>
<summary>✅ Answer</summary>
**B) Delay collection until after breeding season** – Ethical collection requires protecting fauna. Check for nests before collecting and postpone if birds are nesting.
</details>

