CARD 28

What does 'orthodox seed' mean?

A) Seeds that must be sown fresh
B) Seeds that can be dried and frozen for long-term storage
C) Seeds that require fire to germinate
D) Seeds that float in water

<details>
<summary>✅ Answer</summary>
**B) Seeds that can be dried and frozen for long-term storage** – Most Australian natives (Eucalyptus, Acacia) are orthodox. Recalcitrant seeds cannot be stored this way.
</details>

